parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission failure can cause sudden loss of power, stalling, or inability to shift gears, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle hesitates or jerks when shifting gears
fails to shift into gear
or slips out of gear; the transmission leaks fluid; the vehicle stalls or hesitates when accelerating.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Clutch failure can cause the vehicle to stall or hesitate when shifting gears, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor

the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the shift ignition park interlock can cause the vehicle to shift into gear without the driver's intention, leading to accidents or injuries.
